Added support to enable reading template value from file (see updated doc in PR)

```
whisk {
  kubernetes {
    pod-template = "file:/pod-template.yaml"
  }
}
```

So if `pod-template` value is

1. File reference - String representing a file uri `file:/path/to/template.yaml` then its content would be read and used as value
2. Env variable - `pod-template = ${WHISK_POD_TEMPLATE}` then TypeSafe config would internally read its value and use that
3. Literal inline yaml - Else its value would be considered as a literal yaml value

