@markusthoemmes - thanks a lot for your review comments and discussion. Regarding your last comment (https://github.com/apache/openwhisk/pull/4709#discussion_r342501051 you are right, by just letting the inner authorization fail using the Future's failure mode we respond with a http response code 500 (internal server error) which is exactly what I wanted to achieve with the change in this pull request as it allows us to differentiate the case where the entitlement returns unauthorized (403).

I'm going to close this pull request because this change can be achieved by only adapting the iam spi entitlement provider implementation in our service. I don't see the need for doing this change in open right now. Sorry for the inconveniences.
